nts in the Paris Olympics have been tested this year as part of a pre-Games anti-doping programme, the International Testing Agency (ITA) said on July 24.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Testing Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Testing_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9034595830302459, \"rank\": 0.10441831689088907, \"text\": \"ITA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"03:54 AM UpdatedJul\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 396}, {\"ngram\": \"05:10 AM\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 421}, {\"ngram\": \"Nearly 90 per cent\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"all entrants\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"a pre-Games anti-doping programme\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 605}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ITA said it had conducted more than 32,600 doping controls this year, an increase of around 45 per cent on tests of athletes in the previous six months.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9034595830302459, \"rank\": 0.10441831689088907, \"text\": \"ITA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 32,600 doping controls\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"around 45 per cent\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"tests\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous six months\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 765}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It said the testing \\\"led to over 85 cases of potential anti-doping rule violations, resulting in many sanctions and cases that are still ongoing or under review.\\\"\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the testing\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 787}, {\"ngram\": \"over 85 cases\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"potential anti-doping rule violations\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"many sanctions\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"cases\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"review\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 928}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The agency said it had focused on 'high-risk disciplines' in which 75 per cent of Olympic entrants had been tested at least three times.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1068, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The agency\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"'high-risk disciplines\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"75 per cent\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic entrants\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those include weightlifting - which represents a quarter of positive cases in the history of the Summer Olympics - as well as triathlon and open water swimming, where every athlete was tested at least once.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1276, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"weightlifting\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"a quarter\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1126}, {\"ngram\": \"positive cases\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"every athlete\", \"from\": 1237, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics follows at 99 per cent.\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gymnastics\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1287}, {\"ngram\": \"99 per cent\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In track and field - which historically has produced the most failed Olympic tests - the number is 89 per cent.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"the most failed Olympic tests\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1423}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ITA statistics suggest Chinese athletes have been particularly targeted by testers as doping controversy continues to swirl in Paris following the revelation, in April, that23 Chinese swimmers tested positive ahead of the Tokyo Gamesthree years ago but World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada) accepted that they were victims of food contamination.\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Television_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9034595830302459, \"rank\": 0.10441831689088907, \"text\": \"ITA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independen